iv><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qwm1665702782002.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qwm1665702782002.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"qwm1665702782002\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"qwm1665702782002___tan_292104\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Return the tangent of X.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"qwm1665702782002__topic_d90056e1_d90057e1_d90058e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qwm1665702782002__p_d90059e1_d90060e1_d90061e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$tan</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">X</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qwm1665702782002__topic_d59932e1_d59933e1_d59934e1_d59935e1_d59936e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d407151e74\">\n                       \n Parameters\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qwm1665702782002__d6478e20\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">X</var>—angle in radians or a field (or indirect reference to a field), a variable, or a function or expression which evaluates to an angle in radians.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qwm1665702782002__topic_d59937e1_d59938e1_d59939e1_d59940e1_d59941e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d407151e86\">\n                       \n Return Values\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qwm1665702782002__p_d90071e1_d90072e1_d90073e1\">Tangent of <var class=\"keyword varname\">X</var>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qwm1665702782002__p_d90074e1_d90075e1_d90076e1\">If an error occurs , <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span> contains a negative value that identifies the exact error.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"qwm1665702782002__table_d9791e1_d9792e1_d9793e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values of <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span> Commonly Returned Following\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$tan</span>\n</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"qwm1665702782002__table_d9791e1_d9792e1_d9793e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\">\n Value \n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"qwm1665702782002__table_d9791e1_d9792e1_d9793e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">\n Error constant\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"qwm1665702782002__table_d9791e1_d9792e1_d9793e1__entry__3\" rowspan=\"1\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qwm1665702782002__table_d9791e1_d9792e1_d9793e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\">\n -1208\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qwm1665702782002__table_d9791e1_d9792e1_d9793e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">\n &lt;UPROCERR_OVERFLOW&gt;\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qwm1665702782002__table_d9791e1_d9792e1_d9793e1__entry__3\" rowspan=\"1\">\n Overflow.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qwm1665702782002__topic_d59942e1_d59943e1_d59944e1_d59945e1_d59946e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d407151e155\">\n                       \n Use\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qwm1665702782002__p_d90080e1_d90081e1_d90082e1\">Allowed in all component types.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qwm1665702782002__section_ytl_23j_1cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d407151e165\">Example: Using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$tan</span></h2>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<p class=\"p\">The following example returns the tangent of the given expression:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"qwm1665702782002__pre_bsy_23j_1cc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">vTangent = $tan($pi() * RADIANS)</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qxl1719657689828.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$atan</a><p>Return the arc tangent of X.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531459\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531459\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$tan Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 11, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Return the tangent of X. $tan ( X ) Parameters X —angle in radians or a field (or indirect reference to a field), a variable, or a function or expression which evaluates to an angle in radians. Return Values Tangent of X If an error occurs , $procerror contains a negative value that identifies the exact error. Table 1. Values of $procerror Commonly Returned Following $tan Value Error constant Meaning -1208 <UPROCERR_OVERFLOW> Overflow. Use Allowed in all component types. Example: Using $tan The following example returns the tangent of the given expression: vTangent = $tan($pi() * RADIANS) Copy Related Links $atan Return the arc tangent of X. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}